Occasionally giant deepwater squids could be found for sale in the fish markets of [[Waterdeep]].<ref>{{Cite web/theedverse/2019-07-31 - Fish markets of Waterdeep}}

[[Stuffed giant squid]] was a specialty dish, as big as a short [[human]], served at the [[Tulmene's Tower]] inn of [[Tethyr]] in the late 14{{th}} century [[DR]].

Giant squid sepia was a very common [[material component]] in [[spell]]s, particularly those that involved language, detection, and reading. It was used in ''[[erase]]'', ''[[message]]'', ''[[detect magic]]'', and ''[[comprehend languages]]''. The mage [[Casimur]] reported that a form of ''[[darkness, 15' radius]]'' developed by [[Asmiak]] in the ''[[Book of the Silver Talon]]'' could be cast using giant squid sepia, but it had a reduced duration compared to using [[giant octopus]] ink.<ref> Giant river squid [[ink]] was used to paint the magical cards of the [[Edu'sascar]] at [[S'tung Monastery]] in [[T'u Lung]].

A piece of a giant squid tentacle was one of the material components of the ''[[battle tentacles]]'' spell.{{Cite dragon/344/A Dark and Stormy Knight|60}}

Such giant squids could be summoned by the ''[[summon monster IX]]'' spell.
